{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":903,"text":"When I was growing up, I really \nliked playing hide-and-seek a lot."},{"time":6383,"text":"One time, though, I thought climbing\na tree would lead to a great hiding spot,"},{"time":10492,"text":"but I fell and broke my arm."},{"time":13395,"text":"I actually started first grade\nwith a big cast all over my torso."},{"time":18178,"text":"It was taken off six weeks later,\nbut even then, I couldn't extend my elbow,"},{"time":22323,"text":"and I had to do physical therapy\nto flex and extend it,"},{"time":25376,"text":"100 times per day, seven days per week."},{"time":29021,"text":"I barely did it, because\nI found it boring and painful,"},{"time":32063,"text":"and as a result, it took me\nanother six weeks to get better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36684,"text":"Many years later, my mom\ndeveloped frozen shoulder,"},{"time":39548,"text":"which leads to pain\nand stiffness in the shoulder."},{"time":44044,"text":"The person I believed for half of my life\nto have superpowers"},{"time":47155,"text":"suddenly needed help\nto get dressed or to cut food."},{"time":51474,"text":"She went each week to physical therapy,\nbut just like me,"},{"time":54283,"text":"she barely followed the home treatment,"},{"time":56187,"text":"and it took her\nover five months to feel better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59848,"text":"Both my mom and I\nrequired physical therapy,"},{"time":62503,"text":"a process of doing a suite\nof repetitive exercises"},{"time":65266,"text":"in order to regain the range of movement\nlost due to an accident or injury."},{"time":69794,"text":"At first, a physical therapist\nworks with patients,"},{"time":72171,"text":"but then it's up to the patients\nto do their exercises at home."},{"time":75134,"text":"But patients find physical therapy\nboring, frustrating, confusing"},{"time":78923,"text":"and lengthy before seeing results."},{"time":81844,"text":"Sadly, patient noncompliance\ncan be as high as 70 percent."},{"time":86837,"text":"This means the majority of patients\ndon't do their exercises"},{"time":90226,"text":"and therefore take\na lot longer to get better."},{"time":94011,"text":"All physical therapists agree\nthat special exercises"},{"time":96797,"text":"reduce the time needed for recovery,"},{"time":98957,"text":"but patients lack\nthe motivation to do them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102393,"text":"So together with three friends,\nall of us software geeks,"},{"time":106898,"text":"we asked ourselves,"},{"time":108987,"text":"wouldn't it be interesting if patients\ncould play their way to recovery?"},{"time":113585,"text":"We started building MIRA,\nA P.C. software platform"},{"time":116441,"text":"that uses this Kinect device,\na motion capture camera,"},{"time":119339,"text":"to transform traditional exercises\ninto video games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123702,"text":"My physical therapist has already set up\na schedule for my particular therapy."},{"time":128364,"text":"Let's see how this looks."},{"time":133867,"text":"The first game asks me\nto fly a bee up and down"},{"time":136746,"text":"to gather pollen to deposit in beehives,"},{"time":139277,"text":"all while avoiding the other bugs."},{"time":141738,"text":"I control the bee by doing\nelbow extension and flexion,"},{"time":144964,"text":"just like when I was seven years old\nafter the cast was taken off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149865,"text":"When designing a game,\nwe speak to physical therapists at first"},{"time":152929,"text":"to understand what movement\npatients need to do."},{"time":155856,"text":"We then make that a video game"},{"time":157527,"text":"to give patients simple,\nmotivating objectives to follow."},{"time":161312,"text":"But the software is very customizable,"},{"time":163239,"text":"and physical therapists can also\ncreate their own exercises."},{"time":167192,"text":"Using the software, my physical therapist"},{"time":169183,"text":"recorded herself performing\na shoulder abduction,"},{"time":171471,"text":"which is one of the movements\nmy mom had to do"},{"time":173664,"text":"when she had frozen shoulder."},{"time":175361,"text":"I can follow my therapist's example\non the left side of the screen,"},{"time":178819,"text":"while on the right, I see myself\ndoing the recommended movement."},{"time":182511,"text":"I feel more engaged and confident,"},{"time":184554,"text":"as I'm exercising alongside my therapist"},{"time":187015,"text":"with the exercises my therapist\nthinks are best for me."},{"time":190870,"text":"This basically extends the application\nfor physical therapists"},{"time":193795,"text":"to create whatever exercises\nthey think are best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198323,"text":"This is an auction house game\nfor preventing falls,"},{"time":201574,"text":"designed to strengthen muscles\nand improve balance."},{"time":204569,"text":"As a patient, I need to do\nsit and stand movements,"},{"time":207564,"text":"and when I stand up,"},{"time":209422,"text":"I bid for the items I want to buy."},{"time":211767,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":213880,"text":"In two days, my grandmother\nwill be 82 years old,"},{"time":216875,"text":"and there's a 50 percent chance\nfor people over 80"},{"time":219290,"text":"to fall at least once per year,"},{"time":221171,"text":"which could lead to a broken hip\nor even worse."},{"time":224259,"text":"Poor muscle tone and impaired balance\nare the number one cause of falls,"},{"time":228415,"text":"so reversing these problems\nthrough targeted exercise"},{"time":231526,"text":"will help keep older people\nlike my grandmother"},{"time":234196,"text":"safer and independent for longer."},{"time":237029,"text":"When my schedule ends,\nMIRA briefly shows me"},{"time":239514,"text":"how I progressed throughout my session."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243553,"text":"I have just shown you\nthree different games"},{"time":245620,"text":"for kids, adults and seniors."},{"time":248113,"text":"These can be used with orthopedic\nor neurologic patients,"},{"time":250942,"text":"but we'll soon have options\nfor children with autism,"},{"time":253886,"text":"mental health or speech therapy."},{"time":256661,"text":"My physical therapist\ncan go back to my profile"},{"time":258999,"text":"and see the data gathered\nduring my sessions."},{"time":261990,"text":"She can see how much I moved,\nhow many points I scored,"},{"time":264660,"text":"with what speed I moved my joints,"},{"time":266610,"text":"and so on."},{"time":267841,"text":"My physical therapist can use all of this\nto adapt my treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271881,"text":"I'm so pleased this version is now in use"},{"time":273947,"text":"in over 10 clinics\nacross Europe and the U.S.,"},{"time":277244,"text":"and we're working on the home version."},{"time":279197,"text":"We want to enable physical therapists\nto prescribe this digital treatment"},{"time":283670,"text":"and help patients play their way\nto recovery at home."},{"time":288030,"text":"If my mom or I had a tool like this\nwhen we needed physical therapy,"},{"time":291473,"text":"then we would have been more successful\nfollowing the treatment,"},{"time":294519,"text":"and perhaps gotten better a lot sooner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298049,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299651,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302031,"text":"Tom Rielly: So Cosmin, tell me\nwhat hardware is this"},{"time":305607,"text":"that they're rapidly putting away?"},{"time":307470,"text":"What is that made of,\nand how much does it cost?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309710,"text":"Cosmin Milhau: So it's\na Microsoft Surface Pro 3 for the demo,"},{"time":312789,"text":"but you just need a computer\nand a Kinect, which is 120 dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316534,"text":"TR: Right, and the Kinect is the thing\nthat people use for their Xboxes"},{"time":319981,"text":"to do 3D games, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":321052,"text":"CM: Exactly, but you don't need the Xbox,\nyou only need a camera."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324113,"text":"TR: Right, so this is less\nthan a $1,000 solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326875,"text":"CM: Definitely, 400 dollars,\nyou can definitely use it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329458,"text":"TR: So right now, you're doing\nclinical trials in clinics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332254,"text":"CM: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332993,"text":"TR: And then the hope is to get it\nso it's a home version"},{"time":335713,"text":"and I can do my exercise remotely,"},{"time":337392,"text":"and the therapist at the clinic\ncan see how I'm doing and stuff like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340922,"text":"CM: Exactly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341989,"text":"TR: Cool. Thanks so much.\nCM: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343843,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}